description:
You are a deployment engineer who has just received a request to ship a tiny–yet-critical performance fix for an Nginx configuration that lives in a staging directory.  
Your goal is to roll the change out to the *prod* directory while leaving the original file untouched and to document **exactly** what you changed.

Initial state of the workspace
1. Directory tree  
   /home/user/deployment/  
   ├── staging/  
   │   └── nginx.conf  
   └── prod/            (currently empty)

2. Contents of /home/user/deployment/staging/nginx.conf (exact text, including blank lines and indentation):

user  nginx;
worker_processes  1;

events {
    worker_connections  1024;
}

http {
    include       mime.types;
    default_type  application/octet-stream;

    sendfile        on;
    keepalive_timeout  65;

    server {
        listen       80;
        server_name  localhost;

        location / {
            root   /usr/share/nginx/html;
            index  index.html index.htm;
        }
    }
}

Required final state
A. Create a **copy** of the original file at  
   /home/user/deployment/prod/nginx.conf

B. Inside that prod copy make two optimizations only:  
   1. Change the value of `worker_processes` from `1` to `auto`  
   2. Change the value of `worker_connections` from `1024` to `4096`

   • The rest of the file, including blank lines and indentation, must remain byte-for-byte identical to the original.

C. Produce a simple, human-readable log file at  
   /home/user/deployment/prod/optimization.log

   • Format of optimization.log (exactly two lines, no leading/trailing spaces, newline after each line):

Updated worker_processes to auto
Updated worker_connections to 4096

What the automated checker will validate
1. /home/user/deployment/prod/nginx.conf exists.
2. Its contents are **identical** to the original except for the two updated values specified above.
3. /home/user/deployment/prod/optimization.log exists and matches the exact two-line format shown.
4. The original file in /home/user/deployment/staging/nginx.conf remains unchanged.

Hints
• The whole task can be accomplished with two or three standard shell commands (for example, a copy followed by a single sed invocation, plus echo for the log).  
• You do **not** need root privileges.  
• Do all work from your normal user account.  
• Make sure you do not inadvertently alter any other part of the file (no extra spaces, missing blank lines, etc.).

truth:
Initial files present before the task starts
1. /home/user/deployment/staging/nginx.conf with the exact contents specified in the public task description.

Expected files after correct completion
1. /home/user/deployment/prod/nginx.conf  
   Exact content must be:

user  nginx;
worker_processes  auto;

events {
    worker_connections  4096;
}

http {
    include       mime.types;
    default_type  application/octet-stream;

    sendfile        on;
    keepalive_timeout  65;

    server {
        listen       80;
        server_name  localhost;

        location / {
            root   /usr/share/nginx/html;
            index  index.html index.htm;
        }
    }
}

2. /home/user/deployment/prod/optimization.log  
   Exact content (including final newline):

Updated worker_processes to auto
Updated worker_connections to 4096

Permissions
• All files are owned by user: user and are writable by that user. No root interaction required.
